184 Section 25. Section 3C of Act 2025-251, the General
185 Appropriations Act for the fiscal year ending September 30,
186 2026, is hereby amended as follows:
187 "124. Transportation Department of...
188 There is hereby appropriated for payment of the
189 principal of and the interest on all bonds heretofore or
190 hereafter issued for public highways and bridge purposes, or
191 either, by the State of Alabama, Alabama Federal Aid Highway
192 Finance Authority, Alabama Highway Finance Corporation, or
193 Alabama Industrial Access Road and Bridge Corporation, or
194 Alabama Highway Authority, a total of $133,755,861
195 $193,564,457 or so much thereof as may be necessary for
196 payment of said principal and interest at their respective
Page 7

payment of said principal and interest at their respective
SB226 Enrolled
197 maturities, of the revenues pledged for such payment. There is
198 also hereby appropriated an amount not to exceed $25,000,000
199 as an annual contribution to the Alabama Transportation
200 Infrastructure Bank, if needed, for payment of debt service.
201 The Director of Transportation, with the consent of the
202 Governor and the Director of Finance, shall have the authority
203 to transfer any appropriation or any portion thereof between
204 and among subdivisions (a), (b) and (c) of this section
205 whenever such transfer shall be necessary to assure maximum
206 utilization of federal matching funds which shall become
207 available. In the event that there shall not be sufficient
208 funds available for payment of all appropriations hereinabove
209 made, the following provisions shall be applicable. In the
210 event of such insufficiency in respect of said revenues
211 accruing to the Department of Transportation: (1) the
212 appropriation made for Debt Service in subdivisions (a) and
213 (b) hereof shall be paid in full, and (2) the appropriations
214 from the revenues accruing to the Department of Transportation
215 that are herein made for the purposes referred to in
216 subdivisions (a), (b) and (c) except for Debt Service, hereof
217 shall be allocated among the purposes referred to in said
218 subdivisions in such order and with such priorities as the
219 Director of the Department of Transportation shall from time
220 to time direct. The funds appropriated in subdivisions (a) and
221 (c) hereof, for the matching federal funds, shall not revert
222 at the end of the fiscal year for which such appropriations
223 are made but shall remain available for the purposes for which
224 such appropriations were made. In addition to all
Page 8

such appropriations were made. In addition to all
SB226 Enrolled
225 appropriations hereinabove made, there is hereby appropriated
226 to the Department of Transportation all federal funds accruing
227 thereto to be expended only for the purpose for which such
228 funds are made available."
229 Section 26. Notwithstanding any other provisions of
230 this act or any other act, any amounts from appropriations for
231 the fiscal year ending September 30, 2026, to the various
232 state agencies in this act which were unexpended and reverted
233 on September 30, 2026, are hereby reappropriated to the
234 respective offices for the fiscal year beginning October 1,
235 2026.
236 Section 27. This act shall become effective immediately
237 upon its passage and approval by the Governor, or its
238 otherwise becoming law.
